1
00:00:23,865 --> 00:00:26,615
(dramatic music)

2
00:03:22,221 --> 00:03:25,084
- Gentlemen, gentlemen please.

3
00:03:25,084 --> 00:03:27,251
You must take your places.

4
00:03:28,359 --> 00:03:29,192
Gentlemen.

5
00:03:32,789 --> 00:03:35,904
- Ha ha, here's to us before we go

6
00:03:35,904 --> 00:03:39,399
and take that village down below.

7
00:03:39,399 --> 00:03:40,232
- Enough.

8
00:03:41,466 --> 00:03:45,618
Get to your places or
we'll never be on our way.

9
00:03:45,618 --> 00:03:48,973
This is not a time for
drunken celebration.

10
00:03:48,973 --> 00:03:51,800
- Your Grace, we always
celebrate before a raid

11
00:03:51,800 --> 00:03:54,687
and we always drink when we do.

12
00:03:54,687 --> 00:03:56,520
- Shut up, you insect.

13
00:03:58,628 --> 00:04:01,439
This is no game we play.

14
00:04:01,439 --> 00:04:04,559
This painting shall be my legacy,

15
00:04:04,559 --> 00:04:08,835
a record of the beginning
of my reign of greatness.

16
00:04:08,835 --> 00:04:11,418
I think this is my better side.

17
00:04:13,908 --> 00:04:14,741
Shh,

18
00:04:16,024 --> 00:04:17,806
did you hear it?

19
00:04:17,806 --> 00:04:21,177
It's the calm before the storm.

20
00:04:21,177 --> 00:04:24,092
We shall reach down into
that village of weakness

21
00:04:24,092 --> 00:04:26,605
and pull from it that
which will make me the most

22
00:04:26,605 --> 00:04:28,688
powerful man on the earth

23
00:04:30,428 --> 00:04:32,178
The jewel of Polaris.

24
00:04:33,462 --> 00:04:37,629
We shall turn that village
inside out until we find it.

25
00:04:38,696 --> 00:04:42,863
When I have the jewel of
Polaris I will be invincible.

26
00:04:44,462 --> 00:04:46,712
(laughing)

27
00:04:51,838 --> 00:04:52,921
- Your Grace.

28
00:04:54,001 --> 00:04:57,501
I have heard Darbin, the great magician...

29
00:04:59,203 --> 00:05:00,631
- Okay.

30
00:05:00,631 --> 00:05:02,631
- Lives in that village.

31
00:05:04,201 --> 00:05:09,033
He's said to be the most
powerful wizard in all the land.

32
00:05:09,033 --> 00:05:12,088
Are we not to be afraid
of him, Master Falco?

33
00:05:12,088 --> 00:05:15,505
- You dare speak his name in my presence.

34
00:05:17,168 --> 00:05:21,040
For speaking that name
and for doubting my power

35
00:05:21,040 --> 00:05:24,694
your punishment shall
be to never speak again.

36
00:05:24,694 --> 00:05:25,527
- No, no.

37
00:05:34,742 --> 00:05:37,115
- And for any other doubters
now or in the future

38
00:05:37,115 --> 00:05:39,682
the punishment shall be even more severe.

39
00:05:39,682 --> 00:05:40,515
Artist,

40
00:05:42,023 --> 00:05:45,401
a little smaller on the nose I think.

41
00:05:45,401 --> 00:05:47,568
How long we gonna be here?

42
00:05:52,490 --> 00:05:55,449
- Stillness is a virtue, Your Grace,

43
00:05:55,449 --> 00:05:58,032
and patience is its own reward.

44
00:05:59,496 --> 00:06:01,246
- You seem different.

45
00:06:02,609 --> 00:06:05,109
Yesterday you were much taller

46
00:06:08,236 --> 00:06:09,236
and thinner.

47
00:06:12,035 --> 00:06:13,523
Guards,

48
00:06:13,523 --> 00:06:14,773
seize this man.

49
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:21,664
- It's Darbin.

50
00:06:21,664 --> 00:06:25,164
- You are foolish to challenge me old man.

51
00:06:31,656 --> 00:06:34,256
- The jewel of Polaris.

52
00:06:34,256 --> 00:06:38,706
- You have perpetrated
evil far too long Falco.

53
00:06:38,706 --> 00:06:43,264
I will now send you where
you can do harm to no one.

54
00:06:43,264 --> 00:06:47,431
I send you and your shameless
cohorts into the prison

55
00:06:48,522 --> 00:06:49,772
of this canvas.

56
00:06:50,688 --> 00:06:51,521
- No.

57
00:07:18,055 --> 00:07:21,388
(thunder and lightning)

58
00:07:42,598 --> 00:07:44,848
(coughing)

59
00:07:53,405 --> 00:07:56,154
- I will try to protect you

60
00:07:56,154 --> 00:07:58,237
and all who reside herein

61
00:07:59,584 --> 00:08:00,417
with

62
00:08:01,792 --> 00:08:03,542
the jewel of Polaris.

63
00:08:09,022 --> 00:08:11,689
(animal noises)

64
00:08:50,633 --> 00:08:52,883
(coughing)

65
00:09:07,059 --> 00:09:09,809
(dramatic music)

66
00:09:47,869 --> 00:09:52,016
For so long the jewel of
Polaris has been desired

67
00:09:52,016 --> 00:09:53,016
by evil men.

68
00:09:55,672 --> 00:09:58,089
Please protect this treasure.

69
00:09:59,210 --> 00:10:01,540
Only allow a pure individual,

70
00:10:01,540 --> 00:10:04,072
one worthy of its power

71
00:10:04,072 --> 00:10:05,655
to ever possess it.

72
00:10:29,944 --> 00:10:33,271
- Can't five minutes go by
without you annoying me?

73
00:10:33,271 --> 00:10:34,217
- What's your problem?

74
00:10:34,217 --> 00:10:36,147
- You're my problem you little stain.

75
00:10:36,147 --> 00:10:37,730
- Look, I finished.

76
00:10:39,764 --> 00:10:41,909
- Sorry, but it's raining outside.

77
00:10:41,909 --> 00:10:43,851
- So, go up to your sty.

78
00:10:43,851 --> 00:10:45,520
- Can't, carpet's mean on the blade

79
00:10:45,520 --> 00:10:47,037
and besides dad's up there.

80
00:10:47,037 --> 00:10:50,063
- Of course you never do
anything that might annoy him.

81
00:10:50,063 --> 00:10:53,102
- Why annoy him when I can irritate you?

82
00:10:53,102 --> 00:10:55,119
- You spoiled little brat.

83
00:10:55,119 --> 00:10:56,097
- Toro, toro.

84
00:10:56,097 --> 00:10:57,427
- Get out of here.

85
00:10:57,427 --> 00:10:58,971
- Missed me again.

86
00:10:58,971 --> 00:11:01,888
Face it Kim, you throw like a girl.

87
00:11:03,719 --> 00:11:07,383
- You got that part right,
flat as a pancake brother.

88
00:11:07,383 --> 00:11:09,665
Now are you gonna stop
annoying me or do I need

89
00:11:09,665 --> 00:11:10,677
to get rough?

90
00:11:10,677 --> 00:11:14,260
- Rough, rough, rough,
rough, rough, rough.

91
00:11:15,228 --> 00:11:16,978
- Is there a problem?

92
00:11:19,309 --> 00:11:20,142
- No.

93
00:11:21,172 --> 00:11:23,005
- Good, let's go then.

94
00:11:25,073 --> 00:11:26,596
- You're lucky dad came down when he did.

95
00:11:26,596 --> 00:11:28,433
I had you right where I wanted you.

96
00:11:28,433 --> 00:11:30,068
- Yeah, you wish.

97
00:11:30,068 --> 00:11:31,478
I can't believe I have to babysit you two.

98
00:11:31,478 --> 00:11:33,107
- Who you callin' a baby?

99
00:11:33,107 --> 00:11:34,757
- I'm not a baby.

100
00:11:34,757 --> 00:11:37,331
- I know you're not a baby,
Casey, but you weren't

101
00:11:37,331 --> 00:11:38,585
egging them on were you?

102
00:11:38,585 --> 00:11:40,517
- No, I don't like it when they fight.

103
00:11:40,517 --> 00:11:43,491
I just like the loose change
they drop on the ground.

104
00:11:43,491 --> 00:11:45,741
Cleared 65 cents this time.

105
00:11:47,930 --> 00:11:49,930
- Not too bad.

106
00:11:49,930 --> 00:11:52,513
(gentle music)

107
00:12:13,173 --> 00:12:15,857
Okay, here we are kids.

108
00:12:15,857 --> 00:12:16,690
- Bye dad.

109
00:12:16,690 --> 00:12:17,523
- Bye hon.

110
00:12:17,523 --> 00:12:18,781
- Bye dad.

111
00:12:18,781 --> 00:12:20,984
The museum closes at eight, don't be late.

112
00:12:20,984 --> 00:12:21,943
- Take care of the kids for me.

113
00:12:21,943 --> 00:12:24,681
- Don't worry dad, everything will be fine

114
00:12:24,681 --> 00:12:26,931
unless Ben drives me to it.

115
00:12:34,870 --> 00:12:36,992
- You don't have your roller
blades in there, do you?

116
00:12:36,992 --> 00:12:38,601
- No way dad.

117
00:12:38,601 --> 00:12:40,475
You know it's against the
rules to skate in the Museum.

118
00:12:40,475 --> 00:12:41,767
Kim would kill me.

119
00:12:41,767 --> 00:12:43,344
Art supplies.

120
00:12:43,344 --> 00:12:44,875
- Art supplies.

121
00:12:44,875 --> 00:12:45,875
- Later dad.

122
00:13:03,808 --> 00:13:06,232
- Okay, here's the deal, freak.

123
00:13:06,232 --> 00:13:08,886
I like my job at the
museum and I wanna keep it.

124
00:13:08,886 --> 00:13:11,372
So, you go do your art report and try not

125
00:13:11,372 --> 00:13:13,032
to embarrass me or get me fired.

126
00:13:13,032 --> 00:13:13,865
Got it?

127
00:13:14,852 --> 00:13:15,685
- Got it.

128
00:13:18,642 --> 00:13:19,899
- Hello Kim.

129
00:13:19,899 --> 00:13:21,538
- Hi Monty.

130
00:13:21,538 --> 00:13:22,840
- Who's your pretty tag along.

131
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:24,409
- My sister, Casey.

132
00:13:24,409 --> 00:13:26,246
- Nice to meet you Casey, I'm Monty.

133
00:13:26,246 --> 00:13:27,163
- Hi Monty.

134
00:13:28,654 --> 00:13:30,154
- You must be Ben.

135
00:13:32,086 --> 00:13:33,641
Are you the artist in the family?

136
00:13:33,641 --> 00:13:36,158
- The struggling artist.

137
00:13:36,158 --> 00:13:37,285
- Keep practicing.

138
00:13:37,285 --> 00:13:39,202
One day your pictures might
end up on the walls here

139
00:13:39,202 --> 00:13:40,068
at the museum.

140
00:13:40,068 --> 00:13:40,901
- You think so?

141
00:13:40,901 --> 00:13:42,515
- Sure.

142
00:13:42,515 --> 00:13:43,764
- Hey, could we order a pizza?

143
00:13:43,764 --> 00:13:45,477
- Yeah, pizza, pizza.

144
00:13:45,477 --> 00:13:46,728
- We'll see.

145
00:13:46,728 --> 00:13:50,005
As long as you two keep out of trouble.

146
00:13:50,005 --> 00:13:51,999
- Sure, no problem.

147
00:13:51,999 --> 00:13:53,706
- Ben, you need to watch over Casey.

148
00:13:53,706 --> 00:13:55,204
She's your responsibility.

149
00:13:55,204 --> 00:13:56,236
- No way, I got my own plans.

150
00:13:56,236 --> 00:13:57,105
- Ben, I mean it.

151
00:13:57,105 --> 00:13:58,880
- I got my own plans too.

152
00:13:58,880 --> 00:14:00,699
- Ben, you two stick together.

153
00:14:00,699 --> 00:14:02,497
I don't have time to come looking for you.

154
00:14:02,497 --> 00:14:04,523
- All right, all right,
we'll stay together.

155
00:14:04,523 --> 00:14:08,690
Just in case we get separated
we have these walkie talkies.

156
00:14:11,445 --> 00:14:12,790
- Real handful, huh?

157
00:14:12,790 --> 00:14:15,295
Don't worry, I'll check on
'em when I make my rounds.

158
00:14:15,295 --> 00:14:17,973
- Thanks, I'm sure
everything will be fine.

159
00:14:17,973 --> 00:14:18,806
- Bye bye.

160
00:14:18,806 --> 00:14:19,639
- Bye.

161
00:14:21,205 --> 00:14:23,955
(dramatic music)

162
00:14:46,994 --> 00:14:48,694
- The evil Falco depicted in the center

163
00:14:48,694 --> 00:14:51,379
of the painting at right.

164
00:14:51,379 --> 00:14:53,694
Lived in the mid 1600's.

165
00:14:53,694 --> 00:14:57,093
A practitioner of alchemy
and witchcraft, Falco

166
00:14:57,093 --> 00:14:58,995
and his band of outlaws crossed Europe

167
00:14:58,995 --> 00:15:02,822
raiding the countryside
pillaging religious artifacts

168
00:15:02,822 --> 00:15:05,098
believed to bring good fortune.

169
00:15:05,098 --> 00:15:06,596
- Scary looking.

170
00:15:06,596 --> 00:15:08,398
- Everything scares you.

171
00:15:08,398 --> 00:15:09,300
- Look at that one, Ben.

172
00:15:09,300 --> 00:15:12,550
The painter forgot to finish his mouth.

173
00:15:16,268 --> 00:15:18,489
- Freaky looking.

174
00:15:18,489 --> 00:15:21,239
The village painting at the left,

175
00:15:22,165 --> 00:15:26,380
Kaya del Sol was said
to be the last village

176
00:15:26,380 --> 00:15:30,547
raided by Falco before his
mysterious disappearance in 1632.

177
00:15:31,943 --> 00:15:34,342
- Where do you think Falco disappeared to?

178
00:15:34,342 --> 00:15:35,592
- I don't know.

179
00:15:36,927 --> 00:15:39,072
- Got you lookin'.

180
00:15:39,072 --> 00:15:41,167
- You scared the shit outta me.

181
00:15:41,167 --> 00:15:43,284
- Everything scares Ben.

182
00:15:43,284 --> 00:15:46,034
- Speakin' of scary, take a look.

183
00:15:51,088 --> 00:15:53,898
I swear when we first got this painting

184
00:15:53,898 --> 00:15:56,731
Falco's hat was in his other hand.

185
00:15:59,001 --> 00:16:01,405
I figure this painting's haunted.

186
00:16:01,405 --> 00:16:03,721
How about I show you a nicer exhibit?

187
00:16:03,721 --> 00:16:06,197
Probably something more
to your taste, Casey.

188
00:16:06,197 --> 00:16:07,101
What do you say?

189
00:16:07,101 --> 00:16:07,934
- Yeah.

190
00:16:07,934 --> 00:16:09,267
- Yeah, come on.

191
00:16:15,752 --> 00:16:17,606
Now these paintings aren't
as scary as the ones

192
00:16:17,606 --> 00:16:19,849
in the Falco room.

193
00:16:19,849 --> 00:16:22,706
You know, when I just look
at these I get all inspired.

194
00:16:22,706 --> 00:16:24,449
- I like them, too.

195
00:16:24,449 --> 00:16:26,190
- Okay, well look.

196
00:16:26,190 --> 00:16:28,872
I have to finish my rounds
so I'll see you two in a bit.

197
00:16:28,872 --> 00:16:30,374
- Okay, bye Monty.

198
00:16:30,374 --> 00:16:31,207
- Bye bye.

199
00:16:36,490 --> 00:16:39,148
- Yeah, I'm inspired, too.

200
00:16:39,148 --> 00:16:43,065
- Put those on and you're
destined for trouble.

201
00:16:46,057 --> 00:16:48,807
(dramatic music)

202
00:16:50,149 --> 00:16:53,482
(thunder and lightning)

203
00:17:05,561 --> 00:17:07,925
My magician is a good magician.

204
00:17:07,925 --> 00:17:09,879
He can make the storm go away

205
00:17:09,879 --> 00:17:12,417
or make that mean Falco guy reappear,

206
00:17:12,417 --> 00:17:14,892
but as a nice person this time.

207
00:17:14,892 --> 00:17:17,917
He could change anyone into anything.

208
00:17:17,917 --> 00:17:19,323
- Well, he can't turn me
into someone who cares,

209
00:17:19,323 --> 00:17:20,156
now can he?

210
00:17:20,156 --> 00:17:23,654
- You aren't leaving
me alone are you, Ben?

211
00:17:23,654 --> 00:17:26,354
- Sorry C, but I gotta check
out that Falco painting again.

212
00:17:26,354 --> 00:17:29,538
- But, it's haunted Monty said.

213
00:17:29,538 --> 00:17:33,168
- Oooo, the painting's alive, Oooo.

214
00:17:33,168 --> 00:17:35,984
- Quit it, I'm not going back in there.

215
00:17:35,984 --> 00:17:37,645
- You're on your own then.

216
00:17:37,645 --> 00:17:38,645
Testing 123.

217
00:17:40,832 --> 00:17:42,976
Bye baby sister.

218
00:17:42,976 --> 00:17:45,475
The ghosts in the
painting are gonna get me.

219
00:17:45,475 --> 00:17:46,308
Bye.

220
00:17:48,054 --> 00:17:50,804
(dramatic music)

221
00:18:07,633 --> 00:18:09,002
- Coffee break?

222
00:18:09,002 --> 00:18:10,585
- All right, Monty.

223
00:18:11,601 --> 00:18:12,434
Thanks.

224
00:18:13,418 --> 00:18:15,165
Did you find my little migraines?

225
00:18:15,165 --> 00:18:16,150
- Yeah, yeah.

226
00:18:16,150 --> 00:18:18,749
Casey's drawin' away,
but Ben he's already got

227
00:18:18,749 --> 00:18:21,201
to the kingdom of boredom
I'm afraid to say.

228
00:18:21,201 --> 00:18:23,854
- That's usually when he gets
himself in the most trouble.

229
00:18:23,854 --> 00:18:26,185
He always seems to stick
his nose just deep enough

230
00:18:26,185 --> 00:18:27,775
to get it broken off.

231
00:18:27,775 --> 00:18:28,980
- Yeah.

232
00:18:28,980 --> 00:18:31,480
- Or get me in trouble trying.

233
00:18:34,908 --> 00:18:37,411
Maybe I should go and check on him.

234
00:18:37,411 --> 00:18:38,791
I'll be back in five.

235
00:18:38,791 --> 00:18:39,624
- Okay.

236
00:18:55,034 --> 00:18:58,367
(thunder and lightning)

237
00:18:59,788 --> 00:19:02,538
(dramatic music)

238
00:19:11,192 --> 00:19:12,330
- Ben,

239
00:19:12,330 --> 00:19:13,163
Ben,

240
00:19:16,927 --> 00:19:19,250
Ben, where are you?

241
00:19:19,250 --> 00:19:20,731
- Don't be such a baby.

242
00:19:20,731 --> 00:19:22,814
I'll be back in a minute.

243
00:19:31,411 --> 00:19:32,994
- Please save me M.

244
00:19:34,794 --> 00:19:37,922
M the Magnificent, he'll
be able to do anything.

245
00:19:37,922 --> 00:19:42,089
I'll give him a big smile
so he can make people laugh.

246
00:19:44,957 --> 00:19:48,349
(sound of laughter)

247
00:19:48,349 --> 00:19:51,099
(dramatic music)

248
00:20:15,650 --> 00:20:17,650
- Are you lookin' at me?

249
00:20:35,540 --> 00:20:37,664
- Renaissance paintings, who cares?

250
00:20:37,664 --> 00:20:38,914
That one sucks.

251
00:20:39,773 --> 00:20:41,773
Modernism, don't get it.

252
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:44,728
Hmm, that's cool.

253
00:20:44,728 --> 00:20:47,478
(dramatic music)

254
00:21:15,036 --> 00:21:17,433
Case, you gotta come see this now.

255
00:21:17,433 --> 00:21:19,317
The paintings, they are haunted.

256
00:21:19,317 --> 00:21:21,484
- You can't scare me, Ben.

257
00:21:25,756 --> 00:21:26,866
- I'm serious, Casey.

258
00:21:26,866 --> 00:21:30,616
There's something really
weird going on here.

259
00:21:37,205 --> 00:21:38,122
Whoa, whoa.

260
00:21:39,648 --> 00:21:40,731
- Hello, Ben.

261
00:21:44,339 --> 00:21:47,089
(dramatic music)

262
00:22:21,788 --> 00:22:24,038
(rumbling)

263
00:22:43,763 --> 00:22:44,680
- Oh, ouch.

264
00:22:56,784 --> 00:22:57,701
Where am I?

265
00:22:59,860 --> 00:23:01,228
- Yeah, they're flickering down here.

266
00:23:01,228 --> 00:23:03,089
Okay, ladies and gentlemen,
give us five minutes.

267
00:23:03,089 --> 00:23:05,189
We'll have the lights back on, okay?

268
00:23:05,189 --> 00:23:06,341
- [Ghostly Voice] You comin' or what?

269
00:23:06,341 --> 00:23:08,674
