00:54:39,800 --> 00:54:41,300
Where's my sister?

806
00:54:42,604 --> 00:54:45,130
- Falco took her and
Danko to the palace jail.

807
00:54:45,130 --> 00:54:47,225
- Okay, so how do we get into the palace?

808
00:54:47,225 --> 00:54:50,238
- We need to see the village
magistrate who's our leader.

809
00:54:50,238 --> 00:54:51,957
He's currently hiding in the forest.

810
00:54:51,957 --> 00:54:53,136
- Well, what are waiting around here for?

811
00:54:53,136 --> 00:54:53,969
Let's go.

812
00:54:56,704 --> 00:54:59,454
(dramatic music)

813
00:55:02,451 --> 00:55:03,489
- I smell rogues.

814
00:55:03,489 --> 00:55:04,477
We better go this way.

815
00:55:04,477 --> 00:55:07,227
- No, no, no, trust me, this way.

816
00:55:10,901 --> 00:55:11,984
- Halt, halt.

817
00:55:13,478 --> 00:55:15,122
- M, take care of them.

818
00:55:15,122 --> 00:55:15,955
- M, take care of them?

819
00:55:15,955 --> 00:55:18,288
(screaming)

820
00:55:25,770 --> 00:55:26,603
- Losers.

821
00:55:35,389 --> 00:55:37,556
What took you two so long?

822
00:55:38,643 --> 00:55:41,000
- Not bad, M, not bad.

823
00:55:41,000 --> 00:55:42,786
- Keep the faith, keep the faith.

824
00:55:42,786 --> 00:55:44,745
Palmay, where we headed to?

825
00:55:44,745 --> 00:55:45,578
Onward.

826
00:55:51,352 --> 00:55:54,102
(dramatic music)

827
00:56:13,097 --> 00:56:17,097
- When I get my hands on
him I'm gonna kill him.

828
00:56:23,072 --> 00:56:24,653
- Ben, can you hear me?

829
00:56:24,653 --> 00:56:26,188
It's Casey, are you there?

830
00:56:26,188 --> 00:56:27,361
- Hello.

831
00:56:27,361 --> 00:56:28,295
- Hey, Ben.

832
00:56:28,295 --> 00:56:29,543
What happened?

833
00:56:29,543 --> 00:56:32,208
I lost you after the picture went through.

834
00:56:32,208 --> 00:56:33,298
- Hey guys, it's Case.

835
00:56:33,298 --> 00:56:36,930
Oh well, the good news is it
worked and he came through.

836
00:56:36,930 --> 00:56:38,212
- I can't believe it worked.

837
00:56:38,212 --> 00:56:39,711
What's he like?

838
00:56:39,711 --> 00:56:41,646
- He's not too bad, but I
don't think he'll be able

839
00:56:41,646 --> 00:56:42,578
to get us home.

840
00:56:42,578 --> 00:56:43,447
- What's wrong?

841
00:56:43,447 --> 00:56:45,838
- I'm in a great deal of pain.

842
00:56:45,838 --> 00:56:46,900
- Oh, okay.

843
00:56:46,900 --> 00:56:47,886
Well,

844
00:56:47,886 --> 00:56:49,918
let me take a look.

845
00:56:49,918 --> 00:56:51,447
Let's see what we've got here.

846
00:56:51,447 --> 00:56:52,555
- Listen, what's the weather like there?

847
00:56:52,555 --> 00:56:53,670
Is it still storming?

848
00:56:53,670 --> 00:56:56,159
- It's still raining really
bad, but why do you care

849
00:56:56,159 --> 00:56:57,859
about the weather here?

850
00:56:57,859 --> 00:56:59,952
Are you in some kinda denial?

851
00:56:59,952 --> 00:57:00,924
- No, Case.

852
00:57:00,924 --> 00:57:02,829
Apparently, part of the
spell is that Kim and I

853
00:57:02,829 --> 00:57:04,351
have to get back there
before the storm ends

854
00:57:04,351 --> 00:57:06,069
or we won't be able to get back at all.

855
00:57:06,069 --> 00:57:07,551
- You guys have to come back.

856
00:57:07,551 --> 00:57:08,662
You just have to.

857
00:57:08,662 --> 00:57:09,980
Can I talk to Kim?

858
00:57:09,980 --> 00:57:10,926
- Not exactly.

859
00:57:10,926 --> 00:57:12,207
- Not exactly?

860
00:57:12,207 --> 00:57:14,235
- Well, Kim's not here right now.

861
00:57:14,235 --> 00:57:16,087
Actually, she's been kidnapped by Falco.

862
00:57:16,087 --> 00:57:17,051
- What?

863
00:57:17,051 --> 00:57:18,680
- It's not my fault she
wanted to stay in the chapel

864
00:57:18,680 --> 00:57:20,008
instead of comin' with me.

865
00:57:20,008 --> 00:57:21,166
I'm sure she's all right though.

866
00:57:21,166 --> 00:57:24,916
Listen, I gotta go so
I'll talk to you later.

867
00:57:26,333 --> 00:57:29,083
(dramatic music)

868
00:57:54,741 --> 00:57:58,353
- Ah, the mysterious damsel in distress.

869
00:57:58,353 --> 00:57:59,411
- Why am I being held here?

870
00:57:59,411 --> 00:58:01,744
- I'll ask the questions, dear.

871
00:58:01,744 --> 00:58:04,293
- Don't call me dear.

872
00:58:04,293 --> 00:58:05,967
- I'm so sorry.

873
00:58:05,967 --> 00:58:07,866
It was very insensitive of me.

874
00:58:07,866 --> 00:58:08,699
Please.

875
00:58:12,525 --> 00:58:13,774
From the look of your
wardrobe I'd say you're one

876
00:58:13,774 --> 00:58:15,575
of Darbin's sorcerer princesses.

877
00:58:15,575 --> 00:58:17,084
Am I right?

878
00:58:17,084 --> 00:58:18,293
- Who is Darbin?

879
00:58:18,293 --> 00:58:19,600
And, where is my brother?

880
00:58:19,600 --> 00:58:20,433
- Oh yes,

881
00:58:22,512 --> 00:58:25,351
the young boy with the magic feet,

882
00:58:25,351 --> 00:58:28,418
another of Darbin's sorcerer apprentices.

883
00:58:28,418 --> 00:58:30,835
Where is your brother indeed?

884
00:58:32,474 --> 00:58:35,019
It's a very good question
and one I'm glad you asked.

885
00:58:35,019 --> 00:58:37,602
Tell me, where is your brother?

886
00:58:40,761 --> 00:58:41,594
Dear.

887
00:58:42,980 --> 00:58:44,863
- It's not my tongue, M.

888
00:58:44,863 --> 00:58:45,946
It's my foot.

889
00:58:47,399 --> 00:58:49,502
- I knew that, I knew that.

890
00:58:49,502 --> 00:58:52,999
Get ready for eternal foot comfort.

891
00:58:52,999 --> 00:58:53,832
Oh, whoa.

892
00:59:00,731 --> 00:59:02,046
Let me try that again.

893
00:59:02,046 --> 00:59:03,043
- No, no, that's all right.

894
00:59:03,043 --> 00:59:04,688
These feet just needed a rest.

895
00:59:04,688 --> 00:59:07,142
They're feeling much better, thank you.

896
00:59:07,142 --> 00:59:08,397
- No, no, no, no, no, I
can do it, I can do it.

897
00:59:08,397 --> 00:59:10,085
I can do it.

898
00:59:10,085 --> 00:59:11,085
Hokus pokus.

899
00:59:16,784 --> 00:59:17,876
- Wow.

900
00:59:17,876 --> 00:59:20,263
These are wonderful.

901
00:59:20,263 --> 00:59:22,468
They're so light and supportive.

902
00:59:22,468 --> 00:59:23,844
- Yes, they are

903
00:59:23,844 --> 00:59:25,511
They look good, too.

904
00:59:27,089 --> 00:59:27,922
Oh yes.

905
00:59:29,205 --> 00:59:31,288
- Smoke, sparks, yelling.

906
00:59:32,925 --> 00:59:33,896
Oh, you two are doing wonders

907
00:59:33,896 --> 00:59:35,919
for our traveling inconspicuously.

908
00:59:35,919 --> 00:59:37,452
- I'm sorry, Ben.

909
00:59:37,452 --> 00:59:40,793
But, these shoes are wonderful.

910
00:59:40,793 --> 00:59:42,533
- Those boots were killin' his arches.

911
00:59:42,533 --> 00:59:43,793
- They're splendid.

912
00:59:43,793 --> 00:59:45,614
Please keep it down.

913
00:59:45,614 --> 00:59:46,612
Can we go?

914
00:59:46,612 --> 00:59:47,994
- Okay, come, follow me.

915
00:59:47,994 --> 00:59:49,102
- They're splendid.

916
00:59:49,102 --> 00:59:53,269
See if you get a Christmas
present from me this year.

917
01:00:05,026 --> 01:00:05,859
- Palmay,

918
01:00:06,716 --> 01:00:07,805
I was worried.

919
01:00:07,805 --> 01:00:08,903
Where have you been?

920
01:00:08,903 --> 01:00:09,736
- Hiding.

921
01:00:09,736 --> 01:00:11,508
Falco's men have taken Danko.

922
01:00:11,508 --> 01:00:12,597
- Yes, I know.

923
01:00:12,597 --> 01:00:16,414
Falco is making Danko shovel
coal into the palace furnace

924
01:00:16,414 --> 01:00:17,650
day and night.

925
01:00:17,650 --> 01:00:20,567
Even big Danko cannot survive that.

926
01:00:22,858 --> 01:00:25,334
Who are your friends?

927
01:00:25,334 --> 01:00:27,617
- This is Ben and M.

928
01:00:27,617 --> 01:00:29,284
- M the Magnificent.

929
01:00:31,105 --> 01:00:33,524
- You know they saved my life.

930
01:00:33,524 --> 01:00:34,973
- Ah, then they are welcome here.

931
01:00:34,973 --> 01:00:36,223
Please come in.

932
01:00:40,619 --> 01:00:43,202
- Have you got anything to eat?

933
01:00:59,412 --> 01:01:02,860
- M, any chance you can turn
this into a root beer float?

934
01:01:02,860 --> 01:01:03,693
- No.

935
01:01:05,673 --> 01:01:08,594
- Falco's rounded up most
of the villagers by now.

936
01:01:08,594 --> 01:01:12,107
The only way Falco will release
our friends and relatives

937
01:01:12,107 --> 01:01:14,561
is an exchange of the jewel.

938
01:01:14,561 --> 01:01:15,894
We must find it.

939
01:01:17,353 --> 01:01:20,560
- Do you have any idea
where we might find Darbin?

940
01:01:20,560 --> 01:01:22,143
Then we are doomed.

941
01:01:24,284 --> 01:01:25,810
- Hey, I can find Darbin.

942
01:01:25,810 --> 01:01:28,776
- Son, you don't know
the danger out there.

943
01:01:28,776 --> 01:01:30,093
- Are you sure about this?

944
01:01:30,093 --> 01:01:32,266
- If I can find Darbin,
then I can use the jewel

945
01:01:32,266 --> 01:01:36,394
as a bargaining chip to get
Kim back and get us home.

946
01:01:36,394 --> 01:01:37,835
It's a no brainer.

947
01:01:37,835 --> 01:01:40,769
Do we have any other choice?

948
01:01:40,769 --> 01:01:42,980
- All right, I'm in.

949
01:01:42,980 --> 01:01:45,398
But, the jewel alone
will not get you home.

950
01:01:45,398 --> 01:01:48,214
You need the staff, too which Falco has.

951
01:01:48,214 --> 01:01:50,469
How are you gonna pull that off?

952
01:01:50,469 --> 01:01:51,479
- How am I supposed to know?

953
01:01:51,479 --> 01:01:53,070
Makin' this up as I go along.

954
01:01:53,070 --> 01:01:55,092
- You don't actually need to find Darbin,

955
01:01:55,092 --> 01:01:56,197
just the map.

956
01:01:56,197 --> 01:01:57,824
- The map.

957
01:01:57,824 --> 01:01:59,322
- Darbin created a map to the jewel.

958
01:01:59,322 --> 01:02:03,845
When he disappeared the
map disappeared with him.

959
01:02:03,845 --> 01:02:04,678
- Darbin.

960
01:02:05,764 --> 01:02:09,097
I think I know that name from somewhere.

961
01:02:09,953 --> 01:02:10,786
Casey, are you there?

962
01:02:10,786 --> 01:02:13,084
- Yeah, what's happenin'?

963
01:02:13,084 --> 01:02:14,348
- Quick, look at the painting.

964
01:02:14,348 --> 01:02:15,765
Who's the artist?

965
01:02:20,672 --> 01:02:23,173
- It says, A. Darbin.

966
01:02:23,173 --> 01:02:26,748
- So the painting must
be the map to the jewel.

967
01:02:26,748 --> 01:02:28,705
Case, do you see any directions or clues

968
01:02:28,705 --> 01:02:30,276
on the village landscape?

969
01:02:30,276 --> 01:02:34,443
- Yeah, it's by a rock with
all these symbols on it.

970
01:02:35,303 --> 01:02:38,957
It's on a scroll that
says, look under the roads.

971
01:02:38,957 --> 01:02:40,013
- Look under the roads.

972
01:02:40,013 --> 01:02:41,506
Great, thanks Case.

973
01:02:41,506 --> 01:02:42,839
Gotta go, later.

974
01:02:43,883 --> 01:02:45,383
- Under the roads.

975
01:02:46,588 --> 01:02:48,669
- There are so many roads to the village.

976
01:02:48,669 --> 01:02:50,830
How do we know which one?

977
01:02:50,830 --> 01:02:53,866
- Don't look at me, I just work for him.

978
01:02:53,866 --> 01:02:55,366
- Under the roads.

979
01:02:56,347 --> 01:02:57,998
I got it.

980
01:02:57,998 --> 01:02:59,852
It's not under any of
the roads in the village,

981
01:02:59,852 --> 01:03:01,307
but I know where it is.

982
01:03:01,307 --> 01:03:02,140
Come on.

983
01:03:03,683 --> 01:03:06,433
(dramatic music)

984
01:03:36,074 --> 01:03:37,787
- I thought the clue was under a road.

985
01:03:37,787 --> 01:03:38,620
- It is.

986
01:03:44,873 --> 01:03:48,510
Like the clue said, under the roads.

987
01:03:48,510 --> 01:03:51,260
(dramatic music)

988
01:04:04,975 --> 01:04:06,975
Darbin's hidden message.

989
01:04:17,145 --> 01:04:19,998
The great jewel of Polaris
can be found in a pit.

990
01:04:19,998 --> 01:04:22,896
The entrance to the cave
can be found 100 paces

991
01:04:22,896 --> 01:04:25,488
from the great stone in the woods.

992
01:04:25,488 --> 01:04:27,860
- That rock is just a
few moments from here.

993
01:04:27,860 --> 01:04:29,977
- The direction to walk
is that which follows

994
01:04:29,977 --> 01:04:31,585
the afternoon shadow.

995
01:04:31,585 --> 01:04:34,087
Before reaching the jewel
deep in the cave's catacombs

996
01:04:34,087 --> 01:04:36,114
challenges await.

997
01:04:36,114 --> 01:04:38,686
- Darbin never made anything easy.

998
01:04:38,686 --> 01:04:41,118
- Mental, physical and psychological tests

999
01:04:41,118 --> 01:04:44,236
must be overcome in order
to possess the great

1000
01:04:44,236 --> 01:04:46,178
jewel of Polaris.

1001
01:04:46,178 --> 01:04:47,783
- Wow, awful lotta trouble to go through

1002
01:04:47,783 --> 01:04:49,283
just to hide a jewel.

1003
01:04:49,283 --> 01:04:52,118
Didn't Darbin know about
safe deposit boxes?

1004
01:04:52,118 --> 01:04:55,782
Would've saved him and us
a lot of time and effort.

1005
01:04:55,782 --> 01:04:57,169
- For anyone less than the strongest,

1006
01:04:57,169 --> 01:04:58,169
the bravest,

1007
01:04:59,613 --> 01:05:01,483
and most intelligent mortal

1008
01:05:01,483 --> 01:05:03,345
shall never exit the cave alive.

1009
01:05:03,345 --> 01:05:04,678
- Leaves me out.

1010
01:05:05,842 --> 01:05:08,464
- You gotta give old
Darbin points for drama.

1011
01:05:08,464 --> 01:05:10,597
What do you say kid?

1012
01:05:10,597 --> 01:05:12,687
- Like I said, no brainer.

1013
01:05:12,687 --> 01:05:15,320
- All right, but when you
get home you tell Casey

1014
01:05:15,320 --> 01:05:17,214
I want a vacation.

1015
01:05:17,214 --> 01:05:19,020
No more battles,

1016
01:05:19,020 --> 01:05:21,136
no more death defying challenges.

1017
01:05:21,136 --> 01:05:23,159
I want a beach,

1018
01:05:23,159 --> 01:05:24,800
a towel,

1019
01:05:24,800 --> 01:05:25,633
a Slurpee.

1020
01:05:27,288 --> 01:05:28,121
Got it?

1021
01:05:28,984 --> 01:05:30,016
- Case, are you there?

1022
01:05:30,016 --> 01:05:31,632
- Yeah, what happened?

1023
01:05:31,632 --> 01:05:33,325
- I found a map.

1024
01:05:33,325 --> 01:05:35,247
- Does that mean you're on your way back?

1025
01:05:35,247 --> 01:05:37,505
- No, we still have a
really long ways to go.

1026
01:05:37,505 --> 01:05:39,672
What's the weather like there?

1027
01:05:39,672 --> 01:05:42,042
- Monty says we haven't got much time.

1028
01:05:42,042 --> 01:05:43,515
- All right, all right, I gotta go.

1029
01:05:43,515 --> 01:05:44,598
Over and out.

1030
01:05:46,882 --> 01:05:49,632
(dramatic music)

1031
01:06:04,131 --> 01:06:06,014
- You should find the rock a few minutes

1032
01:06:06,014 --> 01:06:08,088
beyond those trees.

1033
01:06:08,088 --> 01:06:10,816
The cave entrance should be
somewhere on the other side

1034
01:06:10,816 --> 01:06:11,816
of the hill.

1035
01:06:12,958 --> 01:06:15,378
- Please, take care of yourself then.

1036
01:06:15,378 --> 01:06:16,295
- You, too.

1037
01:06:20,183 --> 01:06:23,146
- Palmay, I put steel tips in
those sneakers, so if anybody

1038
01:06:23,146 --> 01:06:24,979
gives you any trouble.

1039
01:06:27,561 --> 01:06:30,061
You know how to take 'em down.

1040
01:06:31,447 --> 01:06:33,697
(laughing)

1041
01:06:38,000 --> 01:06:39,500
- Hey, here it is.

1042
01:06:42,483 --> 01:06:44,072
Circle of spokes,

1043
01:06:44,072 --> 01:06:47,191
two lines and the shadow,
so we should go this way.

1044
01:06:47,191 --> 01:06:48,123
- Yeah.

1045
01:06:48,123 --> 01:06:50,623
- One, two, three, four, five,

1046
01:06:51,575 --> 01:06:53,192
what's the matter?

1047
01:06:53,192 --> 01:06:54,025
- Nothing.

1048
01:06:54,986 --> 01:06:56,486
- I lost my count.

1049
01:07:00,439 --> 01:07:02,772
One, two, three, four, five,

1050
01:07:04,865 --> 01:07:06,727
what, what's the problem?

1051
01:07:06,727 --> 01:07:08,270
- It's just that you're
not interested in me.

1052
01:07:08,270 --> 01:07:11,156
You never asked questions about me.

1053
01:07:11,156 --> 01:07:12,721
Where's my family?

1054
01:07:12,721 --> 01:07:13,554
Brothers?

1055
01:07:13,554 --> 01:07:14,387
Sisters?

1056
01:07:14,387 --> 01:07:15,438
What are my hobbies?

1057
01:07:15,438 --> 01:07:16,602
Nothing.

1058
01:07:16,602 --> 01:07:18,510
- M, I'm sorry, okay.

1059
01:07:18,510 --> 01:07:20,427
I've got a lot bigger problems
to deal with right now.

1060
01:07:20,427 --> 01:07:21,916
We don't have time for small talk.

1061
01:07:21,916 --> 01:07:23,704
Have we not stopped
once since you got here?

1062
01:07:23,704 --> 01:07:24,537
No.

1063
01:07:26,948 --> 01:07:29,125
Look, as soon as we get
some down time we can chat

1064
01:07:29,125 --> 01:07:30,892
and you can tell me your
whole life story, okay?

1065
01:07:30,892 --> 01:07:34,942
- Well, I am an only child
from a place called Ishing.

1066
01:07:34,942 --> 01:07:37,897
It's like Cleveland only
the weather is better.

1067
01:07:37,897 --> 01:07:40,794
My hobbies, well, my hobbies
include, I love synchronized

1068
01:07:40,794 --> 01:07:44,961
swimming, playing the dulcimer
and strategic needlepoint.

1069
01:07:46,415 --> 01:07:48,937
- M, I just lost my count
again, so if you'll please

1070
01:07:48,937 --> 01:07:50,815
help me out here and be quiet?

1071
01:07:50,815 --> 01:07:52,141
- I'm all out of quiet,

1072
01:07:52,141 --> 01:07:54,058
but I think I can help.

1073
01:07:59,542 --> 01:08:01,201
98 paces.

1074
01:08:01,201 --> 01:08:03,784
So, the entrance is very close.

1075
01:08:11,925 --> 01:08:13,094
- Found the entrance, huh?

1076
01:08:13,094 --> 01:08:15,511
- So, are you comin' or what?

1077
01:08:21,031 --> 01:08:22,433
- You laugh.

1078
01:08:22,433 --> 01:08:24,462
No thank you, no great job M,

1079
01:08:24,462 --> 01:08:26,447
just laughing at my expense.

1080
01:08:26,447 --> 01:08:29,104
I don't know why I do it.

1081
01:08:29,104 --> 01:08:29,937
Come on.

1082
01:08:34,809 --> 01:08:35,809
Oh, my back.

1083
01:08:37,242 --> 01:08:39,992
(dramatic music)

1084
01:08:51,133 --> 01:08:52,747
- This may have been a mistake.

1085
01:08:52,747 --> 01:08:54,952
- Yeah, tell him that.

1086
01:08:54,952 --> 01:08:56,297
- Can you get this thing to work?

1087
01:08:56,297 --> 01:08:58,678
- Now I'm the department of power.

1088
01:08:58,678 --> 01:09:01,717
I can tell Casey got all the
imagination in the family.

1089
01:09:01,717 --> 01:09:03,979
Here, hold on to that.

1090
01:09:03,979 --> 01:09:05,176
Lantern, lantern in my sight,

1091
01:09:05,176 --> 01:09:07,093
give us a little light.

1092
01:09:12,949 --> 01:09:13,887
Voila.

1093
01:09:13,887 --> 01:09:14,843
- Okay, one more time.

1094
01:09:14,843 --> 01:09:18,128
After I get the jewel and the
staff, then what do we do?

1095
01:09:18,128 --> 01:09:20,707
- We go back to the barnyard
where all this started.

1096
01:09:20,707 --> 01:09:22,904
I place the staff into
the haystack and poof,

1097
01:09:22,904 --> 01:09:24,526
away you go.

1098
01:09:24,526 --> 01:09:25,433
- Cool.

1099
01:09:25,433 --> 01:09:26,361
- Maybe cool.

1100
01:09:26,361 --> 01:09:28,267
Remember it'll only work
if it's still storming

1101
01:09:28,267 --> 01:09:29,514
outside the museum.

1102
01:09:29,514 --> 01:09:30,347
Let's go.

1103
01:09:32,000 --> 01:09:34,750
(dramatic music)

1104
01:10:01,102 --> 01:10:02,176
Let's go this way.

1105
01:10:02,176 --> 01:10:04,379
I've been wrong before,
but I have a good feeling

1106
01:10:04,379 --> 01:10:05,629
about this way.

1107
01:10:06,570 --> 01:10:08,820
(mumbling)

1108
01:10:19,508 --> 01:10:21,341
- Hey, check this out.

1109
01:10:22,494 --> 01:10:23,972
These stones probably have something to do

1110
01:10:23,972 --> 01:10:26,203
with the challenges Darbin wrote about.

1111
01:10:26,203 --> 01:10:27,316
What do you think M?

1112
01:10:27,316 --> 01:10:30,039
- No question about it, Ben.

1113
01:10:30,039 --> 01:10:32,093
- What do you think all these
weird symbols are about?

1114
01:10:32,093 --> 01:10:36,260
- I have a feeling we're
going to find out pretty soon.

1115
01:10:37,182 --> 01:10:39,932
(dramatic music)

1116
01:10:48,880 --> 01:10:51,300
- [Ghostly Voice] Only
intelligent pass in,

1117
01:10:51,300 --> 01:10:55,151
thinking freely and able
to use the sixth sense

1118
01:10:55,151 --> 01:10:58,246
will know which stone would
come next in the sequence

1119
01:10:58,246 --> 01:11:02,453
and therefore, should
be placed in the hole.

1120
01:11:02,453 --> 01:11:05,535
- An intelligent person
with a sixth sense?

1121
01:11:05,535 --> 01:11:07,418
What's that supposed to mean?

1122
01:11:07,418 --> 01:11:09,759
- I think ESP is the sixth sense.

1123
01:11:09,759 --> 01:11:12,873
Maybe you should wait til
the stone talks to you.

1124
01:11:12,873 --> 01:11:16,068
- The next stone in the sequence.

1125
01:11:16,068 --> 01:11:17,483
- I think it's the last one.

1126
01:11:17,483 --> 01:11:19,043
It's simple like the first one.

1127
01:11:19,043 --> 01:11:21,704
Maybe they're like bookends.

1128
01:11:21,704 --> 01:11:22,628
- I don't know M.

1129
01:11:22,628 --> 01:11:24,361
Maybe the clue's in the instructions.

1130
01:11:24,361 --> 01:11:25,444
- Let me see.

1131
01:11:27,121 --> 01:11:29,471
(rumbling)

1132
01:11:29,471 --> 01:11:31,936
I don't think I was supposed
to stick my head in the light.

1133
01:11:31,936 --> 01:11:32,769
- What are we supposed to do?

1134
01:11:32,769 --> 01:11:34,034
I can't leave without the jewel.

1135
01:11:34,034 --> 01:11:35,691
- Maybe if you pick the
right stone it'll stop.

1136
01:11:35,691 --> 01:11:37,962
- A sixth sense, a sixth sense.

1137
01:11:37,962 --> 01:11:38,972
- Come on, come on.

1138
01:11:38,972 --> 01:11:39,893
- I don't know.

1139
01:11:39,893 --> 01:11:41,226
- Just pick one.

1140
01:11:46,913 --> 01:11:47,830
- I got it.

1141
01:12:01,456 --> 01:12:03,579
Yeah, a sixth sense.

1142
01:12:03,579 --> 01:12:05,776
First stone, no broken lines.

1143
01:12:05,776 --> 01:12:08,387
Second stone, one broken line.

1144
01:12:08,387 --> 01:12:10,549
Third stone, two broken lines.

1145
01:12:10,549 --> 01:12:13,716
Three, four, five, six, a sixth sense.

1146
01:12:17,502 --> 01:12:19,944
Thank you, thank you.

1147
01:12:19,944 --> 01:12:20,777
- Bravo, bravo.

1148
01:12:20,777 --> 01:12:21,610
- No more calls please.

1149
01:12:21,610 --> 01:12:23,027
We have a winner.

1150
01:12:24,910 --> 01:12:27,229
I'll be signing autographs
out in front of the cave

1151
01:12:27,229 --> 01:12:29,632
in a half hour, so please
tip your waitresses

1152
01:12:29,632 --> 01:12:31,166
and good night.

1153
01:12:31,166 --> 01:12:33,947
- And a good night to you my friend.

1154
01:12:33,947 --> 01:12:34,780
- Uh oh.

1155
01:12:34,780 --> 01:12:35,613
- What's that?

1156
01:12:35,613 --> 01:12:36,446
- Uh oh, what'd I do?

1157
01:12:36,446 --> 01:12:37,279
M.

1158
01:12:37,279 --> 01:12:38,815
- Align the door.

1159
01:12:38,815 --> 01:12:39,648
The door Ben.

1160
01:12:39,648 --> 01:12:40,600
- M, M, can you hear me?

1161
01:12:40,600 --> 01:12:43,328
- Ben, can you hear me?

1162
01:12:43,328 --> 01:12:44,197
- M, can you hear me?

1163
01:12:44,197 --> 01:12:45,049
- Go on Ben.

1164
01:12:45,049 --> 01:12:47,049
I'll meet you out front.

1165
01:12:50,987 --> 01:12:51,820
- Okay.

1166
01:12:53,196 --> 01:12:55,946
(dramatic music)

1167
01:13:03,991 --> 01:13:06,241
- I'm really gonna do this.

1168
01:13:11,151 --> 01:13:13,717
- Case, can you hear me?

1169
01:13:13,717 --> 01:13:16,085
- Yep, loud and clear.

1170
01:13:16,085 --> 01:13:17,269
- M and I got separated.

1171
01:13:17,269 --> 01:13:18,487
What's the weather update?

1172
01:13:18,487 --> 01:13:21,529
- It's still thundering,
but it's stopped raining.

1173
01:13:21,529 --> 01:13:22,978
Ben, are you okay?

1174
01:13:22,978 --> 01:13:24,533
- No, I'm not.

1175
01:13:24,533 --> 01:13:27,012
I'm really scared Casey.

1176
01:13:27,012 --> 01:13:29,679
- Oh Ben, I wish I was with you.

1177
01:13:35,104 --> 01:13:35,937
- Great,

1178
01:13:36,875 --> 01:13:37,958
room service.

1179
01:13:39,060 --> 01:13:41,762
Compliments to the chef.

1180
01:13:41,762 --> 01:13:44,136
I think I ordered the brown slop,

1181
01:13:44,136 --> 01:13:45,598
not the green slop.

1182
01:13:45,598 --> 01:13:47,181
But, thanks anyway.

1183
01:13:52,069 --> 01:13:54,819
(dramatic music)

1184
01:14:05,618 --> 01:14:08,474
- [Ghostly Voice] You have
entered the final chamber.

1185
01:14:08,474 --> 01:14:11,790
Only a mortal strong of
body and mind shall pass

1186
01:14:11,790 --> 01:14:13,784
the ultimate test.

1187
01:14:13,784 --> 01:14:17,176
To get to the jewel of
Polaris you must prove

1188
01:14:17,176 --> 01:14:19,055
you are worthy

1189
01:14:19,055 --> 01:14:20,222
or die trying.

1190
01:14:21,829 --> 01:14:24,579
(dramatic music)

1191
01:14:49,593 --> 01:14:50,464
- They went in the cave?

1192
01:14:50,464 --> 01:14:51,830
- Yes, Your Grace.

1193
01:14:51,830 --> 01:14:52,747
- Oh goody.

1194
01:14:54,729 --> 01:14:56,471
We've got them.

1195
01:14:56,471 --> 01:14:59,221
(dramatic music)

1196
01:15:38,996 --> 01:15:42,663
- Benjamin Scotound,
you get me out of here.

1197
01:15:52,614 --> 01:15:53,947
- Uh oh, busted.

1198
01:16:02,599 --> 01:16:05,470
- I wouldn't do that if I were you.

1199
01:16:05,470 --> 01:16:07,031
- Who is that?

1200
01:16:07,031 --> 01:16:09,864
- It is I, Darbin and who are you?

1201
01:16:10,788 --> 01:16:13,882
A boy who has successfully
reached this room

1202
01:16:13,882 --> 01:16:17,861
looking for the jewel
of Polaris, I presume.

1203
01:16:17,861 --> 01:16:18,940
- Yeah, my name is Ben

1204
01:16:18,940 --> 01:16:20,620
and I'm lookin' for the jewel.

1205
01:16:20,620 --> 01:16:24,045
- Do you wish to have it
so you can use its power?

1206
01:16:24,045 --> 01:16:26,862
- Yeah, but I'm not gonna use it for evil.

1207
01:16:26,862 --> 01:16:29,129
I came from the future with my sister

1208
01:16:29,129 --> 01:16:32,077
and we accidentally arrived
the same time as Falco.

1209
01:16:32,077 --> 01:16:34,570
- Falco, I banished him to the canvas.

1210
01:16:34,570 --> 01:16:36,570
- Yeah, well he escaped.

1211
01:16:37,683 --> 01:16:41,285
- Ben, you are not in here by accident.

1212
01:16:41,285 --> 01:16:44,481
You were sent here to help stop Falco.

1213
01:16:44,481 --> 01:16:48,648
Without you the village and
the world will not survive.

1214
01:16:50,040 --> 01:16:54,232
Your future will not exist if
Falco takes over the present.

1215
01:16:54,232 --> 01:16:56,496
You must help them.

1216
01:16:56,496 --> 01:16:59,246
If you do you will help yourself.

1217
01:17:00,324 --> 01:17:03,114
- I just don't know if I can stop Falco.

1218
01:17:03,114 --> 01:17:04,614
- Close your eyes.

1219
01:17:06,090 --> 01:17:07,340
Open your mind.

1220
01:17:08,683 --> 01:17:10,016
Open your heart.

1221
01:17:11,722 --> 01:17:13,305
Now open your hand.

1222
01:17:20,027 --> 01:17:21,694
The jewel of Polaris

1223
01:17:22,621 --> 01:17:23,454
is yours.

1224
01:17:30,518 --> 01:17:31,851
- Thanks Darbin.

1225
01:17:57,945 --> 01:17:59,571
- I'll take the jewel.

1226
01:17:59,571 --> 01:18:01,112
- Where's M?

1227
01:18:01,112 --> 01:18:03,869
- Your crazy friend is Falco's prisoner.

1228
01:18:03,869 --> 01:18:05,728
He said when he gets his magic wand back

1229
01:18:05,728 --> 01:18:08,823
he will turn us all into turkeys.

1230
01:18:08,823 --> 01:18:11,934
Give us the jewel now
and we won't kill you

1231
01:18:11,934 --> 01:18:13,702
and your friends.

1232
01:18:13,702 --> 01:18:14,831
- You want the jewel?

1233
01:18:14,831 --> 01:18:17,018
Sure, no problem,

1234
01:18:17,018 --> 01:18:17,851
go fetch.

1235
01:18:19,053 --> 01:18:21,803
(dramatic music)

1236
01:18:40,896 --> 01:18:42,428
- You're okay now Ben.

1237
01:18:42,428 --> 01:18:43,845
We've got a plan.

1238
01:18:56,735 --> 01:19:00,120
- Your friend has evaded
my men and is in possession

1239
01:19:00,120 --> 01:19:01,722
of the jewel.

1240
01:19:01,722 --> 01:19:03,751
- He's not my friend, he's my brother

1241
01:19:03,751 --> 01:19:05,703
and I don't care what he has.

1242
01:19:05,703 --> 01:19:07,926
- Well, I hope he's more
cooperative than you are

1243
01:19:07,926 --> 01:19:12,721
because if he doesn't give
me the jewel by sunrise

1244
01:19:12,721 --> 01:19:15,388
tomorrow will be your final day.

1245
01:19:16,961 --> 01:19:18,711
- Could we eat first?

1246
01:19:22,289 --> 01:19:23,122
- Shut up.

1247
01:19:24,446 --> 01:19:27,196
(dramatic music)

1248
01:19:50,485 --> 01:19:51,485
- Hey buddy.

1249
01:19:59,987 --> 01:20:00,898
- Sorry M.

1250
01:20:00,898 --> 01:20:01,731
- It's okay.

1251
01:20:01,731 --> 01:20:02,916
It had a warranty.

1252
01:20:02,916 --> 01:20:04,598
And I still have the receipt.

1253
01:20:04,598 --> 01:20:05,431
- Quiet.

1254
01:20:07,983 --> 01:20:10,956
You may have bested my
guards, but your friend

1255
01:20:10,956 --> 01:20:14,240
and your sister are still my prisoners.

1256
01:20:14,240 --> 01:20:16,317
If you give me the jewel

1257
01:20:16,317 --> 01:20:18,167
I will not harm them.

1258
01:20:18,167 --> 01:20:21,161
In fact, I will set them free.

1259
01:20:21,161 --> 01:20:23,470
Now you can't get fairer than that.

1260
01:20:23,470 --> 01:20:24,465
- Don't do it Ben.

1261
01:20:24,465 --> 01:20:25,786
- Listen to Kim, Ben.

1262
01:20:25,786 --> 01:20:28,274
He'll never stick to his word.

1263
01:20:28,274 --> 01:20:30,191
- First, set them free.

1264
01:20:31,338 --> 01:20:33,019
Then, you can have it.

1265
01:20:33,019 --> 01:20:34,177
- Ben, no.

1266
01:20:34,177 --> 01:20:35,344
- My pleasure.

1267
01:20:42,708 --> 01:20:43,708
- He's good.

1268
01:20:46,274 --> 01:20:48,642
- Now, give me the jewel.

1269
01:20:48,642 --> 01:20:51,030
- You must promise me you'll
never use it for evil.

1270
01:20:51,030 --> 01:20:51,863
- No evil?

1271
01:20:53,562 --> 01:20:55,229
You're asking a lot.

1272
01:20:57,173 --> 01:20:58,006
All right.

1273
01:20:58,902 --> 01:20:59,902
It's a deal.

1274
01:21:01,205 --> 01:21:02,038
You.

1275
01:21:02,038 --> 01:21:03,205
- No, Ben, no.

1276
01:21:05,404 --> 01:21:07,154
- I give you my word.

1277
01:21:14,936 --> 01:21:19,698
At last (laughing) foolish child.

1278
01:21:19,698 --> 01:21:23,865
Evil is too kinda word for
what I plan to do with you.

1279
01:21:31,982 --> 01:21:34,815
Oh I'm glad you find that amusing.

1280
01:21:42,976 --> 01:21:45,354
- Lookin' for this?

1281
01:21:45,354 --> 01:21:46,187
Or this?

1282
01:21:58,597 --> 01:22:02,413
Falco, you're not wanted
here or anywhere else.

1283
01:22:02,413 --> 01:22:05,445
I send you and your men
back where you belong,

1284
01:22:05,445 --> 01:22:07,320
back into the painting.

1285
01:22:07,320 --> 01:22:08,153
- No.

1286
01:22:15,381 --> 01:22:17,964
(upbeat music)

1287
01:22:36,989 --> 01:22:39,128
- Quiet please, thank you.

1288
01:22:39,128 --> 01:22:40,919
That was very nice.

1289
01:22:40,919 --> 01:22:42,009
Palmay.

1290
01:22:42,009 --> 01:22:43,192
- Thank you magistrate.

1291
01:22:43,192 --> 01:22:46,750
We want to thank you Ben
for saving this village.

1292
01:22:46,750 --> 01:22:48,629
Please kneel.

1293
01:22:48,629 --> 01:22:51,712
We award you with our Medal of Honor.

1294
01:22:54,617 --> 01:22:55,617
- Thank you.

1295
01:22:56,874 --> 01:22:59,549
I wish I could say my trip was wonderful,

1296
01:22:59,549 --> 01:23:02,323
but it's been a little crazy.

1297
01:23:02,323 --> 01:23:04,712
First of all, I'd like to thank Palmay.

1298
01:23:04,712 --> 01:23:09,024
Although he's a little person
he's got a really big heart.

1299
01:23:09,024 --> 01:23:12,333
And finally, I'd like to
thank M the Magnificent.

1300
01:23:12,333 --> 01:23:14,874
Without his help we would not be here.

1301
01:23:14,874 --> 01:23:18,474
With his guidance it
helped me find the jewel

1302
01:23:18,474 --> 01:23:20,846
that will forever protect your village.

1303
01:23:20,846 --> 01:23:23,346
M, I'm sorry I lost your wand.

1304
01:23:26,944 --> 01:23:30,391
You can say something, but
please leave your cursing out.

1305
01:23:30,391 --> 01:23:34,420
It can take a little while
to get used to it, okay.

1306
01:23:34,420 --> 01:23:36,860
- Thank you, thank you one and all.

1307
01:23:36,860 --> 01:23:38,843
I'm so glad you're here.

1308
01:23:38,843 --> 01:23:41,287
It gives me great pleasure to say.

1309
01:23:41,287 --> 01:23:42,285
- Casey?

1310
01:23:42,285 --> 01:23:43,361
- Absolutely nothing.

1311
01:23:43,361 --> 01:23:44,778
- I've got Casey.

1312
01:23:48,997 --> 01:23:49,899
- Casey.

1313
01:23:49,899 --> 01:23:53,188
- Ben, Falco and his men
are back in the picture.

1314
01:23:53,188 --> 01:23:54,924
What did you do?

1315
01:23:54,924 --> 01:23:57,529
- We did good, Case, real good.

1316
01:23:57,529 --> 01:23:59,475
But, we don't have time to
talk about that right now.

1317
01:23:59,475 --> 01:24:00,828
Is it still raining there?

1318
01:24:00,828 --> 01:24:03,200
- No, I think the storm is over.

1319
01:24:03,200 --> 01:24:05,144
- Listen carefully.

1320
01:24:05,144 --> 01:24:07,332
I want you to draw a
picture of a lightning bolt,

1321
01:24:07,332 --> 01:24:08,816
a quick one.

1322
01:24:08,816 --> 01:24:11,033
Put it on the village landscape.

1323
01:24:11,033 --> 01:24:13,496
Do it now and if
everything goes as planned

1324
01:24:13,496 --> 01:24:14,764
we'll be home soon.

1325
01:24:14,764 --> 01:24:15,706
- You got it.

1326
01:24:15,706 --> 01:24:17,446
One lightning bolt comin' up.

1327
01:24:17,446 --> 01:24:18,279
- Roger that.

1328
01:24:18,279 --> 01:24:20,196
Come on guys, let's go.

1329
01:24:32,644 --> 01:24:34,394
Sure hope this works.

1330
01:24:36,612 --> 01:24:38,142
- Ben,

1331
01:24:38,142 --> 01:24:40,741
thank you again for saving
my life and the village.

1332
01:24:40,741 --> 01:24:45,506
I'll make sure that your
memory is never ever forgotten.

1333
01:24:45,506 --> 01:24:48,365
- I'll never forget you man.

1334
01:24:48,365 --> 01:24:50,386
M, I don't know what to say.

1335
01:24:50,386 --> 01:24:51,498
You made it all happen.

1336
01:24:51,498 --> 01:24:52,561
Without you I was lost.

1337
01:24:52,561 --> 01:24:54,208
- Don't sell yourself short.

1338
01:24:54,208 --> 01:24:55,911
You made it happen.

1339
01:24:55,911 --> 01:24:57,171
- What happens to you now?

1340
01:24:57,171 --> 01:25:00,041
- I become an X-Files episode.

1341
01:25:00,041 --> 01:25:00,874
- Cool.

1342
01:25:03,799 --> 01:25:05,814
- Now, you be sure to tell
Casey hello for me, okay?

1343
01:25:05,814 --> 01:25:06,647
- Okay.

1344
01:25:07,997 --> 01:25:10,916
- Now, get the heck outta here.

1345
01:25:10,916 --> 01:25:13,901
- Okay, cross your fingers.

1346
01:25:13,901 --> 01:25:15,234
Oh, spit it out.

1347
01:25:20,194 --> 01:25:22,694
- I send these two into the passageway,

1348
01:25:22,694 --> 01:25:26,111
back into the place from where they came.

1349
01:25:32,403 --> 01:25:34,487
